        <title>The NBA Revolution</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;The NBA is in the midst of a revolution, one that is most obviously seen on offensive side of the ball. When it comes to scoring,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this revolution does come with a trade-off. Teams typically increase versatility by downsizing. Take the Boston Celtics for example, who’s struggles rebounding the basketball are well-known. But when it comes to rebounding, how important exactly is rebounding? And how has this importance changed over the years?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;the-data&quot;&gt;The Data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I used basketball-reference to scrape every box score from the 2016-2017 regular season. For each game, I recorded which team “won” each statistical category, as well as which team ended up winning the game.&lt;/p&gt;

